    "categoryLabel": "Band News",
    "tags": [
      "british-invasion",
      "live-music",
      "60s-tribute",
      "band-intro"
    ],
    "excerpt": "More than just the Beatles — The British Invasion Years brings the entire '60s musical revolution to life on stage. Groovy sights, iconic sounds, both sides of the Atlantic.",
    "body": "You know these songs. You grew up with them, or you inherited them from someone who did. They've been in movies, in commercials, in the back of your mind since before you can remember.\n\nBut there is no substitute for hearing them *live*.\n\nThe British Invasion Years is more than a Beatles tribute. We are a full celebration of the '60s musical revolution — the British acts who stormed America's airwaves and the American acts who rose to meet them. The Beatles, yes. But also The Rolling Stones, The Kinks, The Who, The Animals, The Dave Clark Five, and the homegrown American acts that made the decade one long, glorious musical arms race.\n\nThe band is composed of seasoned professionals — musicians who have played alongside and opened for some of the biggest names in music history. The arrangements are note-for-note. The energy is completely authentic.\n\nFind a show near you on our Tour Dates page. Experience a '60s musical revolution. You already know every word.",
