    "body": "Nestled in the heart of Irwin, Pennsylvania, the historic Lamp Theatre is one of the most beloved intimate concert venues in the greater Pittsburgh area. Built with a rich performing arts legacy and restored to its former glory, The Lamp offers audiences an up-close, personal concert experience that simply doesn't exist in larger arenas.\n\nFor fans of the British Invasion era, this is the *perfect* room. The acoustics are warm, the sightlines are excellent, and the energy inside that house — when the crowd locks in — is electric.\n\nThe British Invasion Years will be taking the Lamp's stage and bringing the full '60s experience to Irwin. Think The Beatles. The Rolling Stones. The Kinks. The Who. The Dave Clark Five. American chart-toppers from the same era — all of it, performed note-for-note by musicians who have played alongside and opened for some of the biggest names in music.\n\nTickets are available now at [lamptheatre.org](https://lamptheatre.org). If you're in the Pittsburgh or Westmoreland County area, this is a night you do not want to miss.",
