    "excerpt": "Music connects people across generations, genres, and geographies. Our connection with the amazing Foxes and Fossils is proof of that — and we're celebrating it.",
    "body": "One of the most genuinely wonderful things about being career musicians is the community that forms around the music — the connections with other artists who share the same love of the craft and the same reverence for the songs that defined an era.\n\nWe're proud to share our connection with Foxes and Fossils — a remarkable act with a deep love for the same classic material that drives everything we do with The British Invasion Years. The common thread? An authentic, heartfelt commitment to songs that matter.\n\nRave on, as they say. The music keeps finding new audiences, new interpretations, and new reasons to matter. And that's the whole point.\n\nCheck out Foxes and Fossils if you haven't already — and keep an eye on our upcoming dates if you'd like to catch The British Invasion Years near you.",
