    "excerpt": "The screaming crowds. The matching suits. The songs everyone knew by heart the second they heard them. The British Invasion Years brings the era of Beatlemania back to life.",
    "body": "There has never been a cultural moment quite like Beatlemania.\n\nIn February 1964, The Beatles landed at JFK Airport and America was simply never the same. The scenes were unprecedented: thousands of screaming fans, round-the-clock media coverage, teenagers glued to their televisions for The Ed Sullivan Show. It wasn't just music — it was a seismic cultural event.\n\nAnd it didn't stop with The Beatles. Within months, the airwaves were flooded with British acts — The Rolling Stones, The Kinks, The Dave Clark Five, The Animals, The Hollies, Herman's Hermits — each bringing their own take on rock and roll to an American audience that simply could not get enough.\n\nThe British Invasion Years exists because those songs, that era, and that energy deserve to be experienced *live*. Not just on Spotify or through a documentary, but in real rooms with real people feeling the music the way it was always meant to be felt.\n\nWe bring Beatlemania back. We bring the whole era back. And when the crowd locks in — you'll understand exactly why this music has lasted 60 years.",
